    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>New technology provides the ultimate in television convenience: viewers will be able to watch anything they want whenever they want. But it also watches viewers, and it could destroy prime time and shatter the power of the mass market. A report by Michael Lewis in The Times Magazine.</p>
